user.name: Aneta Foubíková
user.bio: Photographer from Prague, Czech republic, actually travelling and shooting in New Zealand. Shooting is my hobby. I like nature and animals the most.

results.description: We were camping in the Grand Teton, it was around 8:00 pm just after a short thunderstorm. I was grooving (natural call) and felt someone was looking at me. That was where I found this female deer. I rushed back to get my camera and found her right at our grooving site. We looked at each other closely for a minute, and that’s when I took the picture. I was very excited while taking the picture, not only because of the weird encounter with her but also amazed at how close we were yet she didn’t look like fearing me. Both of us were just curious about each other.
